title: [SPOILERS] Jaime and the army
body:
Surely Jaime has to bring something to Winterfell? I mean, he could at least send a raven to Bronn to gather some of the Lannisters army in the Crownlands or the city guard, or he himself could head off to the Westerlands first and and bring some of his bannermen. Some people here have been saying that the Lannisters generals/bannermen are all too scared of Cersei to go, but WTF??? A huge portion of the Lannisters forces have been destroyed by Daenarys, Drogon and the Dothrakhi… I think they’d know by now that all Cersei has is some Essosi mercenaries. Plus, those that do fear Cersei will fear the dead more. Some others over here said Jaime could be Dany’s military commander if Tyrion vouches for him - do you really expect her to give command over all her armies to Jaime??? Yes, we know that Jaime is a better man than he was years ago, but they don’t - it’d be foolish to trust him and risk angering the North by appointing him. All I’m saying is that Jaime has to bring something to the table, because on his own… well.



Source: https://ift.tt/2DDqWCD

title: [Spoilers] I No Longer Like Daenerys....
body:
So, I was always a big fan of Danny through all 6 seasons. I loved her overall character through those seasons. She had some flaws, but they were forgivable.

But, after watching S7E4, (the attack on the Lannister army), my attitude for her has done a 180. What she did was absolutely brutal, I’d say just as brutal as things Cersei has done.

Also, the way she treated the captives shows rule through fear. And what she did to the Tarleys is scarily reminiscent to her father. I understand the reason for execution, but the method was truly evil.

I think that Daenerys is The Mad Queen.



Source: https://ift.tt/2QhxGYn

summary: I believe that book and show Lyanna are two different people because I refuse to believe that book Lyanna, who didn't want to...
question: I believe that book and show Lyanna are two different people because I refuse to believe that book Lyanna, who didn't want to marry Robert because he can't keep it in his pants would run off to have an affair with a married man with kids. Not unless he had been grooming her. I think he lured her away under false pretenses to get her to meet up with him then abducted her when she didn't want to be his baby incubator.
answer: true (i do hate the show version a lot) but at this point her stans irk me so much i don’t even care
